A junior secondary school pupil of the CAC Grammar School, Akure, the state capital, Emmanuel Ojo, has reportedly died after hitting his head on a panel while attempting to jump through the window. Emmanuel was said to have also hit his head on the concrete floor. Doctors pronounced him dead on arrival at the University of Medical Science Teaching Hospital, Akure where he was rushed to. Late Emmanuel was said to be hale, hearty and bubbling with life when he resumed school on Tuesday but complained of headache.   I’ll succeed Fayemi as Governor, Bamidele boasts     UPDATED: Ebonyi PDP spokesman slumps in court     VIDEO: Pandemonium as Ebonyi PDP Publicity Secretary slumps…   - Advertisement - It was while he was playing that he attempted to jump through the window he hit his head against the panel and landed on the floor with his head on the concrete. The Father of the deceased, Pastor Joshua Ojo, described the incident as a cruel blow of fate on the family. He said he could not query God on why such an incident be allowed to happen to him. Ondo Commissioner for Education, Science and Technology, Mr Olufemi Agagu, who paid a condolence visit to the family, urged the family to take solace in God.